<title>
A-Pillar Outer Panel Removal and Installation
</title>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
The figure below shows condition where following parts are removed.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Front fender 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A9A06005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Hood lock member, lamp support member and lamp support brace 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A9B06001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Cowl side outer member 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A9B06005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Dash side front panel with cowl top side front panel 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A9B06006"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0035.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "56.208mm" ver = "01" gw = "227" gh = "143"/>
</figure>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A9B06009001">
<title>
General Notes
</title>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Welding method and number of welding points are the same on both sides. This repair instruction shows procedure for left side.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The dimensions shown in the figure are reference values when cutting replacement part placed on top of existing part. Determine most appropriate cutting (or joint) line considering both size of replacement part and condition of existing part.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A9B06009002">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Mark at the shown position and cut A-pillar outer panel.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Drill out welding spots.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Bend open metal tab (arrow) and remove A-pillar outer panel.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0037.jpg" width = "183.000mm" height = "210.274mm" ver = "06" gw = "490" gh = "580"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A9B06009003">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Before conducting any weld, check installation position and condition for installation part(s). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A9B04006"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Proceed repair while taking into consideration installation of parts that affect appearance. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A9B04003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install new A-pillar outer panel to vehicle body and cut in stacked condition.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install A-pillar outer panel.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Conduct resistance spot weld and plug weld.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Conduct continuous weld.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply anticorrosion wax to back side of continuous weld part.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Bend in metal tab (arrow) of A-pillar outer panel.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0194.jpg" width = "183.000mm" height = "231.819mm" ver = "01" gw = "497" gh = "641"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.472in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "2.788in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
<symbol name = "MANOTE" width = "5.132mm" height = "3.048mm"/>
:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Conduct resistance spot weld as three panel thickness.
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
